Por clado

### Criar um factor para o agrupamento

plot(tree)
nodelabels(frame="circ", bg="white")

nodes <- c(29,20)
names(nodes) <- c("tomentosa", "pinaster")

plot(tree)
box.clades(tree, nodes=nodes, col=NA, border=c("yellow", "blue"), align = "all")

clades <- rownames(med.spp)
for (i in 1:length(nodes)) {
  nodes[i] -> n0
  descendants(tree, n0, labels=T) -> d0
  clades[match(d0, clades)] <- names(nodes)[i]
}

med.spp[,1] <- as.factor(clades)
colnames(med.spp)[1] <- "clade"

### PCA com as medias

Shifts

### Preparando os dados

pca.spp$li[,1:3] -> surf.dat

tree <- nameNodes(tree)
olist <- convertTreeData(tree, surf.dat)
otree <- olist[[1]]
odata <- olist[[2]]

### Forward

fwd<-surfaceForward(otree, odata, aic_threshold = 0, exclude = 0, verbose = FALSE, plotaic = F)
k<-length(fwd)

fsum<-surfaceSummary(fwd)

  plot(salicifolia[[i]], axes=F, box=F, breaks=brks, col=cols)

}

Diferença

Estimar a expansão / retração

data("wrld_simpl")

threshold = 0.0005 

current -> curr.bin
lgm -> lgm.bin

curr.bin[current[] < threshold] <- 0
curr.bin[current[] >= threshold] <- 1
lgm.bin[lgm[] < threshold] <- 0
lgm.bin[lgm[] >= threshold] <- 1

r.mask <- r.diff <- current

lgm.bin[] - curr.bin[] -> r.diff[]
lgm.bin[] + curr.bin[] -> r.mask[]


curr.bin[curr.bin[] == 0] <- NA
lgm.bin[lgm.bin[] == 0] <- NA
r.mask[r.mask[] == 0] <- NA
mask(r.diff, r.mask) -> r.diff

range(r.diff[], na.rm=T)
## [1] -1  1
brks.d <- c(-1,-0.01,0,0.01,1)
cols.d <- c("yellow", "black", "black", "blue")

par(mfrow=c(1,3))
plot(curr.bin, col="green", legend=F, axes=F, box=F)
plot(wrld_simpl, add=T)
title("Current")
plot(lgm.bin, col="green", legend=F, axes=F, box=F)
plot(wrld_simpl, add=T)
title("LGM")
plot(r.diff, col=cols.d, breaks=brks.d, legend=T, axes=F, box=F)
plot(wrld_simpl, add=T)
title("Difference")

## null device 
##           1

Refúgios

Estimar as regiões estáveis

refuge <- current

lgm.bin[] + curr.bin[] -> refuge[]
refuge[refuge[] < 2] <- NA
rasterToPolygons(refuge, dissolve = T) -> refuge.p

plot(r.diff, col=cols.d, breaks=brks.d, legend=T, axes=F, box=F)
plot(refuge.p, lty="dashed", lwd=2, border="green", add=T)
plot(wrld_simpl, add=T)
title("Stable areas (refuges)")

Range

Estimar a distribuição com um convex hull

### convex hull
gConvexHull(sal.xy) -> sal.chull

par(mfrow=c(1,2))
plot(sal.xy, pch=21, bg="green")
plot(wrld_simpl, add=T)
plot(sal.xy, bg="white", col="white")
plot(wrld_simpl, add=T)
plot(sal.chull, col="green", add=T)

A partir do modelo de distribuição

### Threshold

current -> sal.range
sal.range[sal.range < threshold] <- NA

### Binarizar
sal.range[is.na(sal.range)==F] <- 1

### Identificar clusters de celulas

clump(sal.range) -> sal.range

### Intersectar com os pontos

extract(sal.range, sal.xy) -> e0
na.omit(unique(e0)) -> keep

### Remover clusters que não tem pontos conhecidos

sal.range[which(is.na(match(sal.range[], keep)))] <- NA

### Transformar em polígonos

rasterToPolygons(sal.range, dissolve = T) -> sal.range

### plot

par(mfrow=c(1,2))
plot(sal.xy, pch=21, bg="green")
plot(wrld_simpl, add=T)
plot(sal.xy, bg="white", col="white")
plot(wrld_simpl, add=T)
plot(sal.range, col="green", add=T)
